        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11599.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from William Spottiswoode, 10 July 1878</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5142.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry Willett</ref> does not appear to have any connection with the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7845.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royal Institution of Great Britain</ref>. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3790.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry Richard Hope Pinker’s</ref> letter to CD had not been found.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Spottiswoode was secretary of the Royal Institution (<hi rend="italic">Proceedings of the Royal Institution of Great Britain</hi> 8 (1875–8): 668).</note>
